## 🧾 Conclusion

This analysis explored the relationship between diamond characteristics and price using the ggplot2 diamonds dataset.

### Key takeaways:
- Carat has the strongest influence on diamond price
- Price distribution is highly right-skewed, meaning most diamonds are lower priced
- Cut, color, and clarity also affect pricing, but less strongly than carat
- Higher clarity and better cut generally correspond to higher prices
- A linear regression model can reasonably estimate diamond prices based on physical attributes

### Final insight:
Diamond price is driven primarily by size (carat), while quality features (cut, color, clarity) provide secondary adjustments to pricing.
